io.apptik.rhub

Interface RHub<P>

  • Type Parameters:
    P - the type of Upstream source that the Hub accepts and merged output the Hub returns
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    RSHub<P>, RxJava1Hub, RxJava2ObsHub
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractReactorHub, AbstractRSHub, AbstractRxJava1Hub, AbstractRxJava2ObsHub, AbstractRxJava2PubHub, DefaultReactorHub, DefaultRxJava1Hub, DefaultRxJava2ObsHub, DefaultRxJava2PubHub

    public interface RHub<P>
    Reactive Hub is a collection of multi-receiver and multi-producer Proxies connecting Publishers and Subscribers so that Subscribers can receive events without knowledge of which Publishers, if any, there are, while maintaining easily identifiable connection between them.

    The Hub is fairly simple, it just accepts Publishers or single events and merges them depending on the type of Proxy then returns the resulting Publisher identified by a Tag(topic).

    The Proxy is a single unit, implementation of Roxy (Reactive Proxy) responsible for merge and multicast and possibly buffer the streams of events. The Proxy in a Hub should be kept as simple as possible and free from other processing logic.

    A Hub can have many different proxies identified by a Tag (topic). Every proxy can work independently and merge, buffer and emit events in a different manner.
